    rectoEn: 'The Sharpe ratio benchmarks to recite — and the counter-example that makes them unforgettable?',
    versoEn: 'Passive equities over long periods: ~0.3-0.5. Above 1: excellent. Above 2: no longer impressive — SUSPICIOUS. The counter-example: LTCM posted a Sharpe > 4 before 1998, then lost $4.3bn in a few weeks (m11 ch. 3) — the smooth return came from selling insurance whose tail had simply not yet materialised. The anchor: the scale 0.5 / 1 / 2 / LTCM > 4 recites in one breath — it turns an abstract ratio into a lie detector.',
