    rectoEn: '"My fund did +12%, the market +10%: I have 2% of alpha" — the trap?',
    versoEn: 'WRONG: alpha is not r − r_m — the beta is missing. With β = 1.2, r_f = 3% and a 10% market, the CAPM required 3 + 1.2 × (10 − 3) = 11.4%: alpha is 12 − 11.4 = +0.6%, not 2%. The 1.2 beta is amplification BOUGHT, not manufactured: in a rising market a riskier portfolio MUST beat the index — 1.4 of the 2 points of gap are just normal risk compensation. The anchor: no beta, no alpha — the raw subtraction confuses leverage with talent.',
