    rectoEn: 'The panel: "This hedge fund shows a Sharpe of 3 over five years. Do you invest?"',
    versoEn: 'Reflex: a Sharpe > 2 is viewed with SUSPICION — it is a question, not an answer. The recurring mechanism: strategies that SELL INSURANCE (option writing, credit carry, convergence arbitrage) collect a small regular premium — smooth return, tiny measured volatility, superb Sharpe — while carrying a tail risk that simply has not yet materialised in the window. LTCM: Sharpe > 4, then −$4.3bn in a few weeks (1998). The anchor: ask WHERE the return comes from before admiring the ratio — "show me the distribution, not the standard deviation".',
