    versoEn: 'An index fund QUOTED CONTINUOUSLY like a stock — tradable all day, unlike the mutual fund dealt once a day at NAV. Replication is cheap because a cap-weighted index rebalances ITSELF: when a stock rises, its weight in the index and in the portfolio rise together, with no transaction. The anchor: ~$13 trillion of global assets, fees of 0.05 to 0.4%/year — the machine that industrialised Sharpe\'s arithmetic.',
