    versoEn: 'z = 1.28 for 90%, z = 1.65 for 95%, z = 2.33 for 99% — the desk\'s standard roundings. They plug straight into VaR = V × z × σ × √(h/252): moving from 95% to 99% multiplies the VaR by 2.33/1.65 ≈ 1.41. The anchor: the choice of z is a MANAGEMENT DECISION, not a hidden constant — 95% for daily steering (breach expected ~13 times/year), 99% for the historical regulatory metric (2-3 times/year); and Basel\'s pre-FRTB combination was 99% / 10 days.',
